Odoo Companion — native Linux desktop app
=========================================

A GTK4/Libadwaita app that connects to your own Odoo server over the JSON-RPC
external API and provides desktop notifications, a multi-module dashboard with
charts, a background task timer, and a system-tray indicator.

Install (from a downloaded .deb):
  sudo apt install ./odoo-companion_<version>_all.deb

Run the app:
  odoo-companion

First run:
  Open the Settings tab, enter your Odoo URL, database (click Detect),
  username and password/API key, click Test login, then Save settings.

Background service (keeps notifications running with the window closed):
  systemctl --user status  odoo-companion.service
  systemctl --user restart odoo-companion.service
  systemctl --user enable --now odoo-companion.service   # first session

Floating desktop widget:
  Enabled by default. Shows live worked time, check-in time, live task timer,
  current task, notification count, and idle auto-stop countdown. Drag to move;
  it remembers position. It is partially transparent until hovered. Clicking it
  opens Odoo Companion; hide/disable it from the widget, tray, or Settings.

Timesheet timer protection:
  The task timer warns before idle auto-stop, auto-stops after the configured
  idle limit, and stops when the desktop locks, sleeps, shuts down, reboots, or
  the background service exits. If shutdown happens before Odoo can be updated,
  the corrected stop time is stored locally and retried on the next successful
  poll.

Pages: Dashboard, Attendance, Time Off, Activities, Sales, CRM, Project,
  Purchase, Inventory, Accounting, Expenses, Recruitment, Timer, Timesheets,
  Notifications, Settings. Each data page has charts, filters, search,
  sortable columns and rows that click through to the Odoo record.

Notifications (via libnotify): Discuss messages & channels, Discuss calls,
  inbox mentions, employee check-in/out, server up/down, and reminders
  (no-check-in, stale CRM lead, meeting-soon, helpdesk SLA, running timer).

Privacy:
  Connects only to your configured Odoo URL — no third-party servers.
  Credentials are stored in the system keyring (libsecret).
  Config/state: ~/.config/odoo-companion/  and  ~/.local/share/odoo-companion/

Full documentation, build instructions, and how to publish an APT repository
(so users can `sudo apt install odoo-companion`) are in the project README on
GitHub.

Developed by Rafiur Rahman Rafit (rafiurrahmanrafit.com)
for DotBD Solutions Limited (www.dotbdsolutions.com).
